article_text:
Wichita police are investigating after gunfire was exchanged in the parking lot of an apartment complex.

It happened before 7 p.m. in the Pelican Pointe Apartment Complex.

Wichita police tell KAKE News a pair of cars exchanged gunfire in the parking lot.

Police said several people called to report the gunfire but no one saw the suspects.

Anyone with information is asked to call 911.
